      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>In a letter, December 7, 1965, to Marshall Bean, Kerouac
         states that he works alone and has no secretary to send
         photographs or answer requests, stresses that the organized
         loner is a better creative writer, and gives his personal view
         of God.</p>
